{
  "text": "where \u03b1 is an integration constant. For the solution to be real, it is necessary that \u03bb > 1/3. In paper [CITATION_1] , Park got a more general solution in the IR region when \u03bb = 1, basing on an action softly breaking the detailed balance condition",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "119120343"
